This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the optimization of hyper-parameters in reinforcement learning algorithms. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as RL is a subfield of AI. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as RL is widely used in these fields. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as Bayesian optimization is a popular technique in this field.
